Now I have enough information. Let me create a comprehensive analysis report:

# Design System Alignment Analysis Report

## Analysis Summary

Analyzed 19 showcase files against the new Tailwind v4 CSS-first architecture in `src/styles/`. The showcase files are **remarkably well-aligned** with the new design system, but there are several critical issues that need attention.

---

## Critical Issues

### 1. **Missing Semantic Color Scales (CRITICAL)**

**Location:** Multiple files
**Issue:** The new design system defines semantic colors (`--color-success`, `--color-warning`, `--color-error`, `--color-info`) as single OKLCH values, but showcase files use full 50-950 scales (`success-50` through `success-950`) that don't exist in the new architecture.

**Files Affected:**
- `ColorsSection.vue` (lines 2-8)
- `ComponentsSection.vue` (lines 73-87)
- `FormsShowcase.vue` (lines 170-189)
- `MicroInteractionsShowcase.vue` (lines 237-257)
- `AnimationsSection.vue` (entire file)

**Current Implementation:**
```vue
<!-- ColorsSection.vue line 2-8 -->
{ name: 'Success (Green)', key: 'success', hue: '160', description: 'Success states' },
{ name: 'Warning (Amber)', key: 'warning', hue: '85', description: 'Warning states' },
{ name: 'Error (Red)', key: 'error', hue: '25', description: 'Error states' },
{ name: 'Info (Blue)', key: 'info', hue: '250', description: 'Info states' },
```

**Current Design System (global.css lines 70-75):**
```css
--color-success: oklch(65% 0.17 160);  /* Green */
--color-warning: oklch(75% 0.18 85);   /* Amber */
--color-error: oklch(60% 0.22 25);     /* Red */
--color-info: oklch(65% 0.18 250);     /* Blue */
```

**Why Critical:**
- Users expect 50-950 scales based on showcase documentation
- Badge, button, and form components use non-existent color scales
- Breaking change from documented API

**Recommended Fix:**
Add semantic color scales to `global.css`:

```css
@theme {
  /* Success scale (Green) */
  --color-success-50: oklch(95% 0.03 160);
  --color-success-100: oklch(90% 0.06 160);
  --color-success-200: oklch(80% 0.10 160);
  --color-success-300: oklch(70% 0.13 160);
  --color-success-400: oklch(60% 0.15 160);
  --color-success-500: oklch(65% 0.17 160);  /* Base */
  --color-success-600: oklch(55% 0.15 160);
  --color-success-700: oklch(45% 0.12 160);
  --color-success-800: oklch(35% 0.09 160);
  --color-success-900: oklch(25% 0.06 160);
  --color-success-950: oklch(15% 0.03 160);

  /* Warning scale (Amber) - repeat for warning, error, info */
  /* ... */
}
```

**Impact:** HIGH - Breaks 100+ class usages across showcase files

---

### 2. **Missing Gradient Utilities (CRITICAL)**

**Location:** `GradientsSection.vue`, `Showcase.vue`
**Issue:** Files reference gradient utilities that don't exist in the new design system.

**Missing Utilities:**
- `bg-gradient-hero`
- `bg-gradient-accent-primary`
- `bg-gradient-accent-purple`
- `bg-gradient-accent-warm`
- `bg-gradient-cta`
- `bg-gradient-mesh`
- `text-gradient-primary`
- `text-gradient-purple`
- `text-gradient-warm`

**Files Affected:**
- `GradientsSection.vue` (lines 20-69)
- `GlassSection.vue` (line 18)
- `Showcase.vue` (line 67)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<!-- GradientsSection.vue line 20 -->
<div class="bg-gradient-hero p-8 rounded-xl">
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Add to `utilities.css` in `@layer utilities`:

```css
/* Background Gradients */
.bg-gradient-hero {
  background: radial-gradient(circle at top left, oklch(90% 0.08 200) 0%, transparent 50%),
              radial-gradient(circle at bottom right, oklch(90% 0.08 280) 0%, transparent 50%),
              radial-gradient(circle at center, oklch(95% 0.03 250) 0%, oklch(98% 0.01 200) 100%);
}

.bg-gradient-accent-primary {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-500) 0%, var(--color-primary-700) 100%);
}

.bg-gradient-accent-purple {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7c3aed 0%, #a855f7 100%);
}

.bg-gradient-accent-warm {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f97316 0%, #f59e0b 100%);
}

.bg-gradient-cta {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, var(--color-primary-500) 0%, #7c3aed 100%);
  transition: all var(--duration-normal) ease;
}

.bg-gradient-cta:hover {
  box-shadow: var(--shadow-glow-lg);
  transform: translateY(-2px);
}

.bg-gradient-mesh {
  background: radial-gradient(at 0% 0%, oklch(90% 0.08 200) 0%, transparent 50%),
              radial-gradient(at 100% 0%, oklch(90% 0.08 280) 0%, transparent 50%),
              radial-gradient(at 100% 100%, oklch(90% 0.08 320) 0%, transparent 50%),
              radial-gradient(at 0% 100%, oklch(90% 0.08 340) 0%, transparent 50%),
              oklch(95% 0.03 200);
}

/* Text Gradients - already partially in global.css, consolidate */
.text-gradient-purple {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #7c3aed 0%, #ec4899 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}

.text-gradient-warm {
  background: linear-gradient(135deg, #f97316 0%, #fbbf24 100%);
  -webkit-background-clip: text;
  -webkit-text-fill-color: transparent;
  background-clip: text;
}
```

**Impact:** HIGH - Breaks gradient showcase and hero section

---

### 3. **Missing Typography Utilities (HIGH)**

**Location:** `TypographySection.vue`
**Issue:** References typography utilities that don't exist in CSS files.

**Missing Utilities:**
- `heading-hero`
- `heading-section`
- `heading-card`
- `body-hero`
- `body-large`

**File Affected:** `TypographySection.vue` (lines 73-105)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<!-- TypographySection.vue line 73 -->
<h1 class="heading-hero mb-2">Hero Heading</h1>
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Add to `utilities.css`:

```css
/* Landing Page Typography */
.heading-hero {
  font-size: var(--font-size-display-2xl);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
  letter-spacing: -0.02em;
}

.heading-section {
  font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 4vw, 3.5rem);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-bold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
}

.heading-card {
  font-size: var(--font-size-heading-card);
  font-weight: var(--font-weight-semibold);
  line-height: var(--line-height-tight);
}

.body-hero {
  font-size: clamp(1.25rem, 2vw, 1.5rem);
  line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
}

.body-large {
  font-size: 1.125rem;
  line-height: var(--line-height-relaxed);
}
```

**Impact:** MEDIUM - Only affects typography showcase section

---

## High Priority Issues

### 4. **Missing Semantic Text Color Utilities (HIGH)**

**Location:** Multiple files
**Issue:** Showcase uses semantic text utilities (`text-primary`, `text-secondary`, `text-tertiary`, `text-placeholder`) that aren't defined in design tokens.

**Files Affected:**
- `ColorsSection.vue` (lines 102-130)
- `ComponentsSection.vue` (line 6)
- `TypographySection.vue` (line 10)
- `AnimationsSection.vue` (line 6)
- All showcase files (extensively used)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<p class="text-lg text-secondary">
```

**What Exists:** Only CSS custom properties:
```css
/* These are NOT in @theme, so Tailwind doesn't generate utilities */
--color-text-primary
--color-text-secondary
--color-text-tertiary
--color-text-placeholder
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Move to `@theme` in `global.css`:

```css
@theme {
  /* Text colors - auto-generates utilities */
  --color-text-primary: var(--color-gray-900);
  --color-text-secondary: var(--color-gray-600);
  --color-text-tertiary: var(--color-gray-400);
  --color-text-placeholder: var(--color-gray-400);
}

@theme dark {
  --color-text-primary: var(--color-gray-100);
  --color-text-secondary: var(--color-gray-400);
  --color-text-tertiary: var(--color-gray-500);
  --color-text-placeholder: var(--color-gray-500);
}
```

**Impact:** HIGH - Used in 200+ locations across showcase

---

### 5. **Missing Custom Variant Classes (HIGH)**

**Location:** `AnimationsSection.vue`
**Issue:** Uses `transition-fast`, `transition-base`, `transition-medium`, `transition-slow` that aren't defined.

**File Affected:** `AnimationsSection.vue` (lines 56-67)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<button class="btn-base btn-md bg-primary-500 text-white transition-fast hover:bg-primary-600">
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Add to `utilities.css`:

```css
.transition-fast {
  transition-duration: var(--duration-fast);
  transition-timing-function: ease-out;
}

.transition-base {
  transition-duration: var(--duration-fast);
  transition-timing-function: ease-out;
}

.transition-medium {
  transition-duration: var(--duration-normal);
  transition-timing-function: ease-out;
}

.transition-slow {
  transition-duration: var(--duration-slow);
  transition-timing-function: ease-out;
}
```

**Impact:** MEDIUM - Only affects animation showcase

---

## Medium Priority Issues

### 6. **Inconsistent Dark Mode Pattern (MEDIUM)**

**Location:** Multiple files
**Issue:** Mix of inline dark mode utilities and missing dark variants.

**Example - ComponentsSection.vue line 36:**
```vue
<!-- Inline dark mode (correct) -->
<span class="text-sm font-mono bg-gray-100 dark:bg-gray-800 px-3 py-1 rounded">
```

**Example - ColorsSection.vue line 67:**
```vue
<!-- Missing dark border variant -->
<div class="bg-surface-primary p-6 rounded-lg border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 hover:scale-105 transition-transform">
```

**Why This Matters:**
The design system has `--color-border-primary` defined, but it's not in `@theme`, so no `border-primary` utility is generated.

**Recommended Fix:**
Add to `@theme`:

```css
@theme {
  --color-border-primary: var(--color-gray-200);
  --color-border-secondary: var(--color-gray-300);
  --color-border-focus: var(--color-primary-500);
  --color-border-error: var(--color-error-500);
}

@theme dark {
  --color-border-primary: var(--color-gray-700);
  --color-border-secondary: var(--color-gray-600);
}
```

Then simplify usage:
```vue
<!-- Before -->
<div class="border border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700">

<!-- After -->
<div class="border border-primary">
```

**Impact:** MEDIUM - Quality of life improvement

---

### 7. **Missing Purple Color Scale (MEDIUM)**

**Location:** `GlassSection.vue`
**Issue:** References `purple-*` colors that aren't in the design system.

**File Affected:** `GlassSection.vue` (lines 23, 31, 59, 63)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<div :class="i % 2 === 0 ? 'bg-primary-400' : 'bg-purple-400'">
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Add purple scale to `global.css`:

```css
@theme {
  /* Purple (Accent) */
  --color-purple-50: oklch(95% 0.03 300);
  --color-purple-100: oklch(90% 0.06 300);
  --color-purple-200: oklch(80% 0.10 300);
  --color-purple-300: oklch(70% 0.13 300);
  --color-purple-400: oklch(60% 0.16 300);
  --color-purple-500: oklch(55% 0.18 300);  /* Base: #7c3aed */
  --color-purple-600: oklch(50% 0.16 300);
  --color-purple-700: oklch(40% 0.13 300);
  --color-purple-800: oklch(30% 0.10 300);
  --color-purple-900: oklch(20% 0.07 300);
  --color-purple-950: oklch(15% 0.04 300);
}
```

**Impact:** MEDIUM - Only affects glass showcase visuals

---

### 8. **Missing Pink/Orange Color Scales (MEDIUM)**

**Location:** `GlassSection.vue`
**Issue:** References `pink-*` and `orange-*` colors.

**File Affected:** `GlassSection.vue` (lines 32, 87, 88)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<div class="absolute top-1/2 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 -translate-y-1/2 w-48 h-48 bg-pink-500 rounded-full blur-3xl opacity-40"></div>
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Add pink and orange scales to `global.css` or use existing colors:

```css
@theme {
  /* Pink (Accent) */
  --color-pink-300: oklch(80% 0.15 340);
  --color-pink-500: oklch(65% 0.20 340);

  /* Orange (Accent) */
  --color-orange-300: oklch(80% 0.15 50);
  --color-orange-500: oklch(70% 0.20 50);
}
```

**Impact:** LOW - Only affects glass showcase background visuals

---

## Low Priority Issues

### 9. **Hardcoded Transition Durations (LOW)**

**Location:** Multiple files
**Issue:** Inline transition durations instead of using design tokens.

**Examples:**
- `ColorsSection.vue` line 45: `hover:scale-110 transition-transform`
- `ComponentsSection.vue` line 65: `lift on hover with enhanced shadow`

**Current Pattern:**
```vue
<div class="hover:scale-110 transition-transform">
```

**Better Pattern:**
```vue
<div class="hover:scale-110 transition-transform duration-fast">
```

**Why This Matters:**
Using `duration-fast` (200ms) ensures consistency with animation constants.

**Impact:** LOW - Cosmetic consistency improvement

---

### 10. **Missing Cyan/Blue Color Scales (LOW)**

**Location:** `GlassSection.vue`
**Issue:** References `cyan-*` and `blue-*` colors.

**File Affected:** `GlassSection.vue` (lines 76-78)

**Current Usage:**
```vue
<div class="relative rounded-2xl overflow-hidden bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-100 to-cyan-100 dark:from-blue-900 dark:to-cyan-900 p-8">
```

**Recommended Fix:**
Add to `global.css` or replace with existing info color:

```css
@theme {
  /* Blue (Info) - already have --color-info */
  --color-blue-100: oklch(90% 0.05 250);
  --color-blue-900: oklch(25% 0.10 250);

  /* Cyan */
  --color-cyan-100: oklch(90% 0.05 210);
  --color-cyan-400: oklch(70% 0.12 210);
  --color-cyan-900: oklch(25% 0.08 210);
}
```

**Impact:** LOW - Only affects glass showcase examples

---

## Positive Findings (What's Working Well)

1. **Excellent OKLCH Usage** - Primary and gray scales are perfectly implemented
2. **Consistent Component Classes** - All `btn-*`, `card-*`, `badge-*` classes align with `components.css`
3. **Proper Dark Mode Syntax** - Uses `dark:` variant correctly throughout
4. **Accessibility First** - Excellent use of `motion-safe:`, `aria-*`, proper focus rings
5. **SSR Safety** - Proper use of `useMounted()` composable in Showcase.vue
6. **Modern CSS Features** - Great use of `clamp()`, container queries, custom variants
7. **Glass Effects Perfect** - All glass utilities (`glass-subtle`, `glass-medium`, etc.) exist and work
8. **Shadow System Complete** - All shadow utilities (`shadow-xs` through `shadow-2xl`) are defined
9. **Form Components Excellent** - All form utilities (`form-control-base`, `checkbox-wrapper`, etc.) exist

---

## Summary of Required Changes

### Must Fix (Breaks Functionality)
1. Add semantic color scales (success-*, warning-*, error-*, info-* 50-950)
2. Add gradient utilities (bg-gradient-*, text-gradient-*)
3. Add typography utilities (heading-*, body-*)

### Should Fix (Improves DX)
4. Add text color utilities to @theme (text-primary, text-secondary, etc.)
5. Add transition speed utilities (transition-fast, transition-base, etc.)
6. Add border color utilities to @theme (border-primary, etc.)

### Nice to Have (Polish)
7. Add purple/pink/orange/cyan color scales
8. Standardize transition durations

---

## Recommendations

1. **Create Missing Utilities File**: Create `src/styles/missing-utilities.css` with all missing utilities, then import into `global.css`
